@startuml V22 Pipeline
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam activityBackgroundColor #F0F8FF
skinparam activityBorderColor #4682B4
skinparam activityDiamondBackgroundColor #FFF8DC
skinparam activityDiamondBorderColor #DAA520
skinparam arrowColor #4682B4
skinparam noteBorderColor #778899
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFFACD

title **AgentLinker V22 — Trace Link Recovery Pipeline**\n(V16 + 5 fixes: generic override, compound-noun guard,\nparent-overlap guard, smaller batches, enhanced judge)

start

partition "**Phase 0: Document Profile**" #E8F5E9 {
  :Load components from PCM model\n& sentences from text file;
  :Compute document statistics:\n• pronoun_ratio\n• mention_density\n• sentences/component ratio;
  :Determine **structural complexity**:\nuncovered_ratio > 0.5 AND spc > 5\n→ complex = True/False;
  note right
    Pure deterministic.
    No LLM calls.
  end note
}

partition "**Phase 1: Model Structure**" #E8F5E9 {
  :Classify components as\n**architectural** vs **ambiguous**;
  note right
    Inherited from AgentLinker.
    Ambiguity labels logged
    but NOT used for decisions.
    Per-mention check instead.
  end note
}

partition "**Phase 2: Pattern Learning**" #E3F2FD {
  :Learn document patterns\nvia **LLM debate** (2-pass);
  :Extract:\n• subprocess_terms\n• action_indicators\n• effect_indicators;
  note right
    Two independent LLM passes
    cross-validate patterns.
    Subprocesses used to filter
    coref/validation later.
  end note
}

partition "**Phase 3: Document Knowledge**" #E3F2FD {
  :LLM Pass 1: Find abbreviations,\nsynonyms, partial references;
  :LLM Pass 2 (Judge): Validate mappings\nREJECT generic / wrong / hallucinated;

  if (Rejected as generic?) then (yes)
    :Apply overrides:;
    :**(Fix A)** CamelCase override\n(e.g. "DataStorage" rescued);
    :Uppercase override\n(short acronyms rescued);
    :Component-name override\n(capitalized non-common terms);
  endif

  :Deterministic CamelCase-split injection\n"ImageProvider" → "Image Provider";

  :Output: **DocumentKnowledge**\n{abbreviations, synonyms,\npartial_references, generic_terms};
}

partition "**Phase 3b: Multi-word Partial Enrichment**" #E8F5E9 {
  :For multi-word components,\ncheck if last word appears ≥3x\nas standalone partial;
  :Auto-add partials\n(e.g. "Backend" → "ServiceBackend");
  note right
    Deterministic.
    Skips if last word <4 chars,
    if another component shares
    the suffix, or if already known.
  end note
}

partition "**Phase 4: TransArc Baseline**" #FFF3E0 {
  :Load TransArc CSV baseline links;
  :Map component IDs → names;
  :Output: **transarc_links**\n(highest priority, immune to judge);
  note right
    TransArc links have 90%+
    precision — never filtered
    or judged downstream.
  end note
}

partition "**Phase 5: Entity Extraction** (Fix D)" #E3F2FD {
  :LLM extracts component references\nfrom document in **batches of 50**\n(timeout: 240s per batch);
  :Match types: exact | synonym |\npartial | functional;
  :Verify matched_text in sentence\n+ generic mention pre-check;
  :Apply **abbreviation guard**:\nreject false abbreviation matches;
  :Output: entity **candidates**\n(need validation);
  note right
    **Fix D**: Smaller batches (50 vs 100)
    + longer timeout (240s vs 120s)
    for more reliable extraction.
  end note
}

partition "**Phase 5b: Targeted Recovery** (Fix C)" #E3F2FD {
  :Identify unlinked components\n(no TransArc + no entity match);

  if (Unlinked components?) then (yes)
    :Per-component LLM search\nfor direct/functional/role refs;
    :**(Fix C)** Parent-overlap guard:\nskip sub-type if parent\nalready linked to sentence;
    :Add extra candidates;
  endif
}

partition "**Phase 6: Validation**" #F3E5F5 {
  :Reject generic mentions\n(single lowercase word in text);

  :Step 1 — **Code-first auto-approve**:\nword-boundary match for\nname/alias in sentence text;
  note right
    Deterministic. Handles
    short names (UI, DB)
    via word-boundary regex.
  end note

  :Step 2 — **2-pass LLM intersect**:\nPass A: actor role focus\nPass B: direct reference focus\n→ approve only if BOTH approve;

  if (Generic-risk component?) then (yes)
    :Step 3 — **Evidence post-filter**:\nLLM must cite exact text\nsubstring as evidence;
    :Verify evidence contains\nalias of target component;
  endif

  :Output: **validated** candidates;
}

partition "**Phase 7: Coreference Resolution**" #E3F2FD {
  if (Complex document?) then (yes)
    :Mode: **debate**\n(20-sentence batches\n+ context window);
  else (no)
    :Build discourse model\n(recent mentions, topic);
    :Mode: **discourse**\n(12-sentence batches\n+ 3-sentence prev context);
  endif

  :Require **antecedent citation**:\n• component name in antecedent sentence\n• within 3 sentences\n• pronoun is grammatical subject;

  :Apply **generic coref filter**:\nsingle-word components need\nrecent mention (2 sentences);

  :Apply **deterministic pronoun coref**:\n"It..." / "As such, it..."\n→ unambiguous lookback (1-3 sents);

  :Output: **coref_links**;
}

partition "**Phase 8: Implicit References**" #FFEBEE {
  #FF8A80:SKIPPED\n(dead weight — adds noise,\nnot enough signal);
}

partition "**Phase 8b: Partial Injection** (Fix B)" #FFF3E0 {
  :For each partial reference\nin doc_knowledge, scan all sentences;
  :Inject links where partial\nappears as clean mention;
  :**(Fix B)** Compound-noun guard:\nblock if short partial (≤3 chars)\nfollowed by common noun\n(e.g. "UI name", "UI type");
  :Output: **partial_inject** links;
}

:**Combine & Deduplicate**\ntransarc + entity + coref + partial\n(keep highest-priority source);

partition "**Phase 8c: Boundary Filters**\n(non-TransArc only)" #FFEBEE {
  :Filter 1: **package_path**\n— name only in dotted path;
  :Filter 2: **generic_word**\n— preceded by modifier word;
  :Filter 3: **weak_partial**\n— partial is a generic word;
  :Filter 4: **abbrev_guard**\n— abbreviation false match;
  note right
    TransArc links are
    **immune** to all filters.
  end note
}

partition "**Phase 9: Judge Review** (Fix E)" #F3E5F5 {
  :Separate **safe** vs **review** links;

  :Safe (skip judge):\n• TransArc links (immune)\n• Standalone component name in text\n• Alias mention in text;

  :For review links,\nbuild cases with context\n(prev sentences, match text, source);

  :**(Fix E)** Enhanced judge prompt\nwith **4 explicit rules**:\n1. REFERENCE (not string-match)\n2. ARCHITECTURAL LEVEL (not impl)\n3. TOPIC (not incidental)\n4. NOT GENERIC (not English word);

  :Union voting (2 passes):\n→ reject ONLY if **both** reject;

  :Output: **approved** links;
}

partition "**Phase 10: FN Recovery**" #FFEBEE {
  #FF8A80:SKIPPED\n(dead weight — unreliable);
}

:Save phase log to JSON;
:Return **final links**;

stop

legend right
  |= Color |= Meaning |
  | <#E8F5E9> | Deterministic (no LLM) |
  | <#E3F2FD> | LLM-based phase |
  | <#F3E5F5> | Multi-pass LLM (voting/intersect) |
  | <#FFF3E0> | Data loading / injection |
  | <#FFEBEE> | Skipped / filtering |
endlegend

@enduml
